Design: card backdrop depicting an underwater scene of a pond; card shapes of various fish etc, each with a staple and marked with a score number; hand made penalties
No. of pieces: 46
No. illustrated: all
fields.title: fishing game
fields.credit: Given by G. D. C. Swain
fields.history_note: The aim of the game is to catch the fish on the line.  The player with the most points wins.   None fish items have no score.
fields.historical_context_note:
Rewards: points scored
Forfeits: see rules
No. of Players: any
Equipment required: catches and an old hat and tin of salmon, penalties
scene


Rules: The set is very similar to other fishing games, however, the donor created an extra group  of fish to change the game from merely being a score taking one.
The extra fish and penalties are of card coloured with crayons and marked in ink.  Each has a bar of metal stapled through it to be caught by the fishing line.  These bars appear to have been cut from tin cans.
Penalties:-
MISS A TURN; TRY AGAIN; IF YOU HAVE 10 FISH PUT 5 BACK; BAD LUCK; PUT BACK A FISH; GOOD LUCK; HAVE ANOTHER GO.
None fish items:-
Diver No Score; Crocradial (sic) 20lbs.; Stool, 1lb; Tin, 11oz; Boot, 8oz.; CHamber Pot, 4oz; Leaf, 8 oz; Chest, 4 lb; Tin of Beef, ¼oz; Shell 1½oz; Drain Pipe, 7oz
